29/09/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- During a visit to Pristina Wednesday (28 September), the commander of NATO's Allied Joint Force Command in Naples, Admiral Harry Ulrich, said the Pact expects no deterioration in the situation in either Kosovo or the region during future status talks.
His statement followed talks with Kosovo President Ibrahim Rugova, who will lead his side's negotiating team.
In other news Wednesday, senior UNMIK and Belgrade officials condemned an attack on the highest-ranking Serb police officer in Kosovo, Colonel Dejan Jankovic.
He was wounded in an ambush on his vehicle near the village of Stari Kacanik Wednesday evening.
(B92, KosovaLive, Tanjug, Beta - 28/09/05)
